<topic xml:id="ha-resources-configuring-groups"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Configuring resource groups</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <xi:include href="../snippets/ha-resources-groups.xml"/>
    </abstract>
  </info>

  <para>
    You can configure resource groups with the &crmshell; (&crmsh;) or with the &hawk; Web interface.
  </para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <title>Requirements</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The primitive resources already exist.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The primitive resources aren't already cloned or included in another group.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <variablelist role="tabs">
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&crmshell;</term>
      <listitem>
        <xi:include href="../snippets/ha-crmsh-procedure-intro.xml"/>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              Log in either as the &rootuser; user or as a user with <command>sudo</command> privileges.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Configure a group. Add the resources in the order you want them to start:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure group <replaceable>GROUP_NAME RESOURCE1 RESOURCE2</replaceable></command></screen>
            <itemizedlist>
              <title>Additional options</title>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  Groups inherit most meta attributes from their primitive resources, but you can
                  also add the <literal>target-role</literal>, <literal>priority</literal>,
                  <literal>maintenance</literal> and <literal>is-managed</literal> meta attributes
                  directly to the group. For example:
                </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure group res-group res1 res2 res3 \
  meta target-role=Started priority=100
</command></screen>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Check the status of the group:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm status</command></screen>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&hawk;</term>
      <listitem>
        <xi:include href="../snippets/ha-hawk-procedure-intro.xml"/>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              In a Web browser, go to
              <literal>https://<replaceable>HAWKSERVER</replaceable>:7630/</literal>
              and log in.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              From the left navigation bar, select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Configuration</guimenu>
              <guimenu>Add Resource</guimenu></menuchoice>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>Group</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Enter a unique <guimenu>Group ID</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              From the list of <guimenu>Children</guimenu>, select the resources to add to the
              group. You can drag and drop the resources into a different order using the icons on
              the right. The resources start in the specified order and stop in the reverse order.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step performance="optional">
            <para>
              Add <guimenu>Meta Attributes</guimenu> by selecting them from the drop-down list.
            </para>
            <para>
              You can hover the cursor over each meta attribute to see a description.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu> to finish the configuration.
            </para>
            <para>
              A message at the top of the screen shows if the action was successful.
            </para>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <itemizedlist>
    <title>For more information</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <command>crm configure help group</command>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <link xlink:href="https://clusterlabs.org/projects/pacemaker/doc/3.0/Pacemaker_Explained/html/collective.html#groups-a-syntactic-shortcut"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
